Description:
We are Pomerleau. And you could be too.
Pomerleau is recognized as one of Canada’s leaders in the construction industry, in the institutional, commercial, industrial and civil engineering sectors. Clients benefit from our expertise as general contractor, construction manager, project manager and design-builder.
Pomerleau believes in delivering excellence. Every Pomerleau employee upholds this value, leading to the achievement of superior results in every sector where we do business. Pomerleau: proud individuals who share a vision and are passionate about what they do.
What YOU Will Do
Design, handle, and perform the follow-up and the approval of special equipment and special tools intended with the construction methods;
Analyze the various plans and specs;
Draw up the list of project requirements with regard to temporary equipment and structures;
Put together the preliminary work schedule;
Develop manpower curves relating to the schedule;
Take part in the transfer meeting with the production team;
Confirm and finalize construction methods with the construction team;
Put together various documents, namely construction site installation plans as well as the plans which are specific to the project;
Design temporary structures—formwork, envelope, access, etc.;
Sign and seal construction plans;
Provide technical support to the production team on construction sites.
What YOU Will Bring
Bachelor’s degree in civil engineering or in construction engineering;
Member of Engineers and Geoscientist BC;
5+ years’ experience in the civil construction industry;
Marine experience considered an asset;
Solid written and verbal communication skills;
Strong computer skills with enthusiasm for innovation;
Excellent analytical skills and sound technical knowledge;
Proficiency in Excel, AutoCAD, MS Project, Primavera, Civil 3D, Advance Design America, Revit software;
Ability to exercise initiative and promote the quest for results.
